A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 7 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to the imposition, rate, computation, exemptions, and credits for state income tax,
3 so as to exclude up to $10,000.00 of overtime wages per employee from taxation; to provide
4 for reporting by employers; to provide reporting by the department to the General Assembly;
5 to provide for a sunset date; to provide for related matters; to provide for a short title; to
6 provide for legislative purpose; to provide for an effective date and applicability; to repeal
7 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Overtime Income Tax Exemption Act."
11 SECTION 2.
12 The purpose of this Act is to reduce the tax burden on workers who earn overtime pay,
13 incentivize productivity, and promote economic fairness for hourly employees.
